<P><HI>What&s;oever GOD doeth is Well done.</HI></P>
<P>A Di&s;cour&s;e Deliver'd at <HI>New-Salem, <HI>May</HI></HI> 20th, 1739, Being the next Sabbath after the <HI>Funeral</HI> OF Mrs. <HI>Anna Lovett,</HI> CONSORT of the Reverend Mr. <HI>Jo&s;eph Lovett,</HI> Pa&s;tor of the Church of CHRIST in that Place. AND Now Publi&s;h'd at the De&s;ire &amp; Expence of that Pari&s;h.</P>
<P><HI>By</HI> George Beckwith, <HI>M. A. <HI>Pa&s;tor of a Church in</HI></HI> Lyme.</P>
<Q><BIBL><HI>P&s;al. xlvi. 10.</HI></BIBL>
<P>Be &s;till, and know that I am GOD&mdash;.</P></Q>
<Q><BIBL><HI>1 Sam. iii. 18.</HI></BIBL>
<P>&mdash;It is the LORD: Let him do what &s;eemeth him good.</P></Q>
<P><HI>N. LONDON,</HI> Printed &amp; Sold by T GREEN. 1739</P>
</DIV1>
